6. Main Method Working
The line public static void main(String[] args) is the entry point of any Java application.
●	public: It must be accessible by the JVM to start the program.
●	static: The JVM can call this method without creating an instance (object) of the class first.
●	void: It doesn't return any value.
●	main: The specific name the JVM looks for to start execution.
●	String[] args: This allows the program to accept inputs from the user at the moment the program starts.
