2. Relational Operators
These compare two values and always return a boolean (true or false). Unlike JavaScript/TypeScript, Java does not have ===; the == operator is the standard for primitives.
Operator	Description	Example
==	Equal to	5 == 3 (false)
!=	Not equal to	5 != 3 (true)
