4. Bitwise Operators
These perform operations on the individual bits (0s and 1s) of a number. While less common in web development, they are extremely fast for low-level logic.
●	& (Bitwise AND): Sets each bit to 1 if both bits are 1.
●	| (Bitwise OR): Sets each bit to 1 if one of two bits is 1.
●	^ (Bitwise XOR): Sets each bit to 1 if only one of two bits is 1.
●	~ (Bitwise NOT): Inverts all the bits.
Example: 5 (0101) & 3 (0011) = 1 (0001)
