6. Ternary Operator
This is a shorthand for an if-else statement. It is very popular in Full Stack development for keeping code concise, especially when passing data to the frontend.
Syntax: variable = (condition) ? valueIfTrue : valueIfFalse;
Example Code:
Java
int marks = 75;
String result = (marks >= 40) ? "Pass" : "Fail";
System.out.println(result); // Output: Pass
