When to use throws vs. try-catch
Scenario	Use throws?	Use try-catch?
You can't fix the error inside the method.	Yes (Pass it up)	No
You want the calling method to decide the fix.	Yes	No
You are at the "top level" (like a UI button click).	No	Yes (Handle it here)
You want the program to keep running after a failure.	No	Yes
