Why It Matters
●	Before JDK 5: You had to manually wrap and unwrap primitives using methods like Integer.valueOf() and intValue().
●	After JDK 5: Autoboxing/unboxing makes code cleaner and more intuitive.
●	Use Case: Collections (ArrayList, HashMap) only store objects, so primitives must be boxed into wrappers.
