3. Advanced Operations: FlatMap and Reduce
FlatMap (Flattening nested structures)
If you have a list of lists (like a classroom of students, where each student has a list of grades), flatMap "flattens" them into a single stream of values.
Java
List<List<String>> complexList = Arrays.asList(
    Arrays.asList("Java", "Spring"),
    Arrays.asList("Python", "Django"),
    Arrays.asList("SQL", "NoSQL")
);

List<String> flatList = complexList.stream()
    .flatMap(List::stream) // Flattens the nested lists into one stream
    .collect(Collectors.toList());

System.out.println(flatList); // [Java, Spring, Python, Django, SQL, NoSQL]
Reduce (Aggregating)
reduce takes a stream and collapses it into a single value (like a sum or a concatenated string).
Java
List<Integer> costs = Arrays.asList(10, 20, 30);

// Start with 0, and add each element to the running sum
int total = costs.stream()
    .reduce(0, Integer::sum); 

System.out.println("Total Cost: " + total); // 60
