        boolean noneNegative = numbers.stream().noneMatch(n -> n < 0);

        System.out.println("All even? " + allEven);           // true
        System.out.println("Any > 5? " + anyGreaterThanFive); // true
        System.out.println("None negative? " + noneNegative); // true
    }
}
Explanation:
●	allMatch() → checks if all elements satisfy a condition.
●	anyMatch() → checks if at least one element satisfies a condition.
●	noneMatch() → checks if no elements satisfy a condition.
●	These are terminal operations returning boolean results.
